Property Documentation

◆ RefId

String^ IonicSecurity::SDK::CreateKeysRequest::Key::RefId
getset

The reference ID.

Parameters
[in]msRefIdThe reference ID.

The reference ID is an arbitrary string provided by callers in order to track created keys between the request and response. The order of the keys returned in the response is not guaranteed to be the same as the order of the request. When creating multiple keys the reference ID is required in order to associate the keys returned in the response with the keys requested.

For example, if the request object specifies three keys, then the response object may contain those keys in any order. The correlation of key request to key response is determined by the reference ID.
